### 1. Rename this file to fd3d_config.
### 2. Uncomment appropriate lines to control the behavior of fd3d.
### The scope of fd3d_config depends on the location of the file as follows.
### - (location): (scope)
### - individual project directory: the project directory
### - the parent directory of individual project directories: all project directories in the directory
### - $FD3D_ROOT: any project directories
### fd3d_config with a narrower scope overrides the one with a wider scope.
### For example, if you put fd3d_config in an individual project directory, then it ignores all settings described in $FD3D_ROOT/fd3d_config.


